Package models

Contains classes responsible for application logic.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AddStrategy
    This interface is used as a parent for methods which add single events to some user's event manager.
    Resource
    An object representing an external resource.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DisplayState
    An object representing currently displayed week.
    Event
    Implements whole Event model, used to store Tasks and locate them in time.
    EventGroup
    This class wraps events which belong to the same group.
    EventHandler
    This class provides methods for event handling.
    EventSet
    A set of events.
    FirstPossibleEvent
    This class provides a method which returns the earlier - the better non-overlapping position of a event in a event handler.
    LastPossibleEvent
    This class provides a method which returns the latter - the better non-overlapping event to be fit into the handler.
    Model
    Silence is golden.
    Organizer
    Singleton representing current application state.
    ResourceFile
    An object representing a file.
    ResourceLink
    An object representing a link.
    Task
    Part of an event.
    User
    A box for storing basic user data.
    UserManager
    This class provides methods for user management.
    UserProfile
    Instances of this class store unique properties and management tools for a particular user.
    UserSet
    A set of users.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    EventPriority
    This class contains constant enum values representing event priorities.
